Explanation:

The problem requires finding the minimum number of moves needed to make the given string a palindrome. We can solve this problem by iterating through the string half way, comparing adjacent characters, and swapping them if they are not the same. Since we only need to iterate once, the time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the string. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the input string and do not require any additional data structures. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few simple operations.

